Judgment on bail for the alleged Parliament arsonist will be handed down on Friday. Zandile Mafe appeared in court earlier today. eNCA's Ayesha Ismail is following this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The alleged Parliament arsonist Zandile Mafe will remain in police custody until next week Friday. He appeared at the Cape Town Regional Court on Saturday to make another bid for bail. This comes after his lawyers argued he was denied this opportunity twice. READ: Parliament Fire | Mafe speaks out about mental illness stigma Earlier this month, Mafe’s defence challenged in court his referral for a 30-day psychiatric observation. He was then released from Valkenberg Hospital and incarcerated at Pollsmoor Prison. Mafe says the state should not fear that he will run away if granted bail.